$ VBScript: writing colored output to the console

This is an attempt to create a → development/languages/VBScript[VB Script] that creates → design/graphic/color[colored] output on the console when run with → Windows/dirs/Windows/System32/cscript_exe[`cscript.exe`].

gh|about-VBScript|/examples/colored-output.vbs||

sa:
 → Windows/development/Portable-Executable/subsystem/console#win-virtual-terminal-sequences[Virtual Terminal Sequences on Windows]

  The value of → Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_CURRENT_USER/console#reg-console-VirtualTerminalLevel[`VirtualTerminalLevel`] under the registry key
  → Windows/registry/tree/HKEY_CURRENT_USER/console[`HKEY_CURRENT_USER\Console`].

  The same technique can also be used in → development/databases/Oracle/SQL-Plus to → development/databases/Oracle/SQL-Plus#sql-plus-colors[color its output].

  The PowerShell cmdlets → Windows/PowerShell/modules/personal/console/write-textInConsoleXColor[`write-textInConsoleErrorColor` and `write-textInConsoleWarningColor`].

links:
    → https://stackoverflow.com/a/38815213/180275[This stackoverflow answer] was very useful.
